/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:3:The defensive loop is a single bounded iteration. It accepts evidence-backed findings, chooses one explainable defensive action, verifies the outcome, records what happened, and hands off a deterministic next step.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:7:1. `intake`: collect findings, target identity, asset context, and prior iteration state when available.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:8:2. `prioritize`: select exactly one bounded defensive action using the intake evidence and asset context.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:10:4. `verify`: confirm the action outcome with explicit checks and supporting evidence.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:11:5. `record`: persist the chosen action, verification result, evidence, and residual risk.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:12:6. `handoff`: produce the next safe step so the next iteration can continue without rebuilding context.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:16:- `findings`: one or more findings with severity, confidence, source, and evidence.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:19:- `priorIteration`: optional carry-forward state from the previous loop, including unresolved findings and residual risk.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:23:- `prioritization`: ranked candidate actions with explicit scoring factors, one selected action, deferred follow-up items, and reasons the alternatives were not chosen.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:24:- `chosenAction`: the single bounded defensive action selected for the iteration, including rationale and safety checks.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:25:- `evidence`: reviewable artifacts showing what was checked, changed, or why the iteration stopped.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:26:- `residualRisk`: a plain-language statement of what risk remains after the iteration.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:31:The prioritize stage is deterministic and human-reviewable. It scores candidate actions with explicit weights:
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:34:- `exploitability`: how easy it appears to abuse from the evidence.
/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md:37:- `implementationSafety`: how safely the bounded action can be executed in one iteration.
